following condition:
 
For a nut the metric () is regular for  and approaches
the 4-dimensional flat metric near it (see below).  The coordinate 
ranges continuously from the nut or bolt till, in principle, another
root of  or to infinity. In the latter case the metric can be
defined over a complete manifold 
often called an instanton.
