value of  which in turn will determine the locations of the bolt
in each of the  bolt solutions. In general the periodicities
are different for different choices of base manifolds and the explicit
form of  will be different in each case and for each
possible value of . However, Taub-Bolt would be used for all of
them in the same way Schwarzschild is used generically irrespective of
the choice of base.

Apart from the  regular bolt solutions, another regular
solution exists for the degenerate case of  by taking limits in the
same way we have obtained the Eguchi-Hanson metric in the case of four
dimensions (see below). Also at the limit  one obtains
the Schwarzschild metric. However, these are only a subset of
Schwarzschild metrics in even dimensions. The Taub-NUT family being
even dimensional cannot offer any Schwarzschild metric in odd
dimensions. Therefore one obtains only the sub-class of Schwarzschild
metrics with Einstein-Ka hler base in any even dimension from the
Taub-NUT family and any odd dimensional Schwarzschild metric is
precluded automatically.
