Series Expansions 
The expressions () and () are exact and can be used
for precise calculation using the known properties of the higher order
hypergeometric functions (see, for example,
). However, in many situations, approximations via series
expansions in powers of the parameter are useful along with the exact
solutions. Obtaining such series for () and () is
nontrivial through their direct expansions. However, such series can
be obtained directly from () by use of Lagrange
expansion. If
 
